sks.json`. Archive any completed tasks older than 30 days to `data/tasks-archive.json`. Log count.\n\n4. **Backup Check**: Check if `/Volumes/OpenClaw-WD` or `/Volumes/Public` is mounted. Check if today's backup file exists. Log result.\n\n5. **Daily Summary**: Append a brief summary to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` with: date, system health snapshot, git commit status, tasks archived, backup status.\n\n6. **Telegram Sitrep**: Use `curl` to send a one-line daily sitrep to Telegram chat 7507878944 via the OpenClaw gateway message API. The sitrep should include: tasks active count, tasks awaiting review count, disk %, and overall status (nominal/fail). Format example:\n   `📡 DAILY SITREP — 2026-05-16 | 3 active · 1 awaiting review · 85% disk · ✅ ALL SYSTEMS NOMINAL`\n   \n   If disk > 90% or any critical issues found, use `⚠️` instead and note the issue.\n   \n   Use the OpenClaw gateway to send: `openclaw message send --channel telegram --to 7507878944 \"<sitrep text>\"` or use the gateway HTTP API at localhost:18789.\n\nKeep it fast. Use exec for all operations. Do not call any models.","timeoutSeconds":120},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"last","to":"7507878944"},"state":{"lastRunAtMs":1779400800006,"lastRunStatus":"error","lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":120222,"lastDeliveryStatus":"unknown","consecutiveErrors":1,"consecutiveSkipped":0,"lastFailureNotificationDeliveryStatus":"unknown","lastError":"cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)","lastDiagnostics":{"summary":"cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)","entries":[{"ts":1779400920227,"source":"cron-setup","severity":"error","message":"cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)"}]},"lastDiagnosticSummary":"cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)","lastErrorReason":"timeout"},"updatedAtMs":1779452312353}],"total":4,"offset":0,"limit":4,"hasMore":false,"nextOffset":null,"deliveryPreviews":{"e9be709d-ca66-463a-8499-9adb