{"type":"message","id":"2e69d23b","parentId":"4cd33c84","timestamp":"2026-05-28T08:54:26.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see several issues:\n\n1. The LaunchAgent exited and `KeepAlive` should have restarted it but didn't (exit code 143 = SIGTERM, probably got stuck on a TimeMachine permission error)\n2. The `start-mc.sh` script uses `sed -i ''` to modify `build-info.ts` in-place, which means repeated starts corrupt the git state (but trees are clean now)\n3. There are also warnings about API route files that don't export a Route\n\nLet me fix these now. First, let me kill any old processes and restart properly:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"2174f36d-b826-47f6-932b-abc678e756a4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pkill -f \"vite.*3000\" 2>/dev/null; pkill -f \"mission-control\" 2>/dev/null; sleep 1; lsof -i :3000 2>/dev/null | head -3; echo \"---\"; lsof -i :3001 2>/dev/null | head -3","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"pkill -f \\\"vite.*3000\\\" 2>/dev/null; pkill -f \\\"mission-control\\\" 2>/dev/null; sleep 1; lsof -i :3000 2>/dev/null | head -3; echo \\\"---\\\"; lsof -i :3001 2>/dev/null | head -3\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1463,"output":220,"cacheRead":56064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57747,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779958451586,"responseId":"gen-1779958451-prPYoT4kQVq1BBSYKYGe"}}
