{"type":"message","id":"041191b4","parentId":"f3b04a0e","timestamp":"2026-05-28T10:43:21.430Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGot it — everything I do is in service of helping you. That's the job.\n\nSo to be clear on Aider going forward: **I'll use it for large multi-file refactors** where it shines. For quick one-off edits, the direct tools are faster. The rule of thumb:\n\n- **Aider:** \"Split this 500-line file\", \"Refactor this module\", \"Add X across 10 files\", \"Reorganize this directory structure\"\n- **Direct edit/write:** \"Fix this bug\", \"Add this component\", \"Rename this thing\", \"Delete dead code\"\n- **Sub-agent:** Parallel tasks, research, verification\n\nAll three are tools in the same toolbox. Aider just happens to be the one you specifically set up for me to use on big coding work — and it did well on the Scheduler split. I'll use it properly going forward.\n\nAnything else you want tackled?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":6318,"output":194,"cacheRead":150528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":157040,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779964963664,"responseId":"gen-1779964963-WfwwjD1b5Hw3fbN2Ps8Z"}}
