{"type":"message","id":"cb276c9d","parentId":"c3ae7915-b61f-4622-80e3-6aee16a63cc9","timestamp":"2026-05-28T10:47:13.907Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:7507878944\",\n  \"message_id\": \"2111\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"sender\": \"Andre\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-05-28 11:45 GMT+1\",\n  \"inbound_event_kind\": \"user_request\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Andre (7507878944)\",\n  \"id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"name\": \"Andre\",\n  \"username\": \"mayhomme\"\n}\n```\n\nConversation context (untrusted, chronological, selected for current message):\n#2032 Thu 2026-05-28 08:17 GMT+1 Andre: Do all recommendations\n#2047 Thu 2026-05-28 09:53 GMT+1 Andre: Do it all\n#2065 Thu 2026-05-28 10:37 GMT+1 Andre: So any other recommendations\n#2067 Thu 2026-05-28 10:42 GMT+1 Andre: Yes do! Is this using aider?\n#2069 Thu 2026-05-28 10:42 GMT+1 Andre: Should you be using aider to make this easier\n#2081 Thu 2026-05-28 10:59 GMT+1 Andre: Let’s review it, if the task is to time consuming, let’s skip\n#2091 Thu 2026-05-28 11:23 GMT+1 Andre: When finished with the task, why is aider not being used?\n#2094 Thu 2026-05-28 11:26 GMT+1 Andre: Yes, aider was brought in to improve coding and help you out\n#2095 Thu 2026-05-28 11:27 GMT+1 Andre: Everything is to help you out\n#2100 Thu 2026-05-28 11:36 GMT+1 Andre: 6. AIDER INTEGRATION (IF USEFUL) ═══════════════════════════════ You mentioned Aider could speed up large refactors. If it's worth adding, use it in non-interactive mode: - Install: pip install aider-chat or brew install aider - API key: use our existing OpenRouter key (already in OPENROUTER_API_KEY) - Usage: aider --message \"refactor X across Y files\" --model openrouter/owl-alpha --yes - The --yes flag auto-confirms changes so it runs without interaction - Only use for large mu…[truncated]\n\nAdd this to FRAMEWORK.md under the Build vs Execute section:\n\n## Build Tool Rules\n\nFor coding work on Mission Control or any project, use the right\ntool for the job size:\n\n| Tool | Use For | Example |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| Direct edit/write | Single-file fixes, quick changes | \"Fix this bug\", \"Add this component\", \"Delete dead code\" |\n| Aider (--message --yes) | Multi-file refactors, module splits | \"Split this 500-line file\", \"Refactor imports across 10 files\" |\n| Sub-agents | Parallel tasks, research, verification | \"Review all routes for dead code\", \"Check every component for SSR safety\" |\n\nAider is already installed and configured with OpenRouter. Use\n--message with --yes for non-interactive mode. Never try to drive\nit through interactive TUI or tmux sessions.\n\nDo NOT use OpenClaw chat for complex multi-file coding work. That's\nwhat Aider and direct edits are for. OpenClaw executes, monitors,\nand wires data."}],"timestamp":1779965233901}}
