{"type":"message","id":"da6cbb11","parentId":"8f8c4610","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:21:56.906Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:7507878944\",\n  \"message_id\": \"2136\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"sender\": \"Andre\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-05-28 12:21 GMT+1\",\n  \"inbound_event_kind\": \"user_request\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Andre (7507878944)\",\n  \"id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"name\": \"Andre\",\n  \"username\": \"mayhomme\"\n}\n```\n\nConversation context (untrusted, chronological, selected for current message):\n#2091 Thu 2026-05-28 11:23 GMT+1 Andre: When finished with the task, why is aider not being used?\n#2094 Thu 2026-05-28 11:26 GMT+1 Andre: Yes, aider was brought in to improve coding and help you out\n#2095 Thu 2026-05-28 11:27 GMT+1 Andre: Everything is to help you out\n#2100 Thu 2026-05-28 11:36 GMT+1 Andre: 6. AIDER INTEGRATION (IF USEFUL) ═══════════════════════════════ You mentioned Aider could speed up large refactors. If it's worth adding, use it in non-interactive mode: - Install: pip install aider-chat or brew install aider - API key: use our existing OpenRouter key (already in OPENROUTER_API_KEY) - Usage: aider --message \"refactor X across Y files\" --model openrouter/owl-alpha --yes - The --yes flag auto-confirms changes so it runs without interaction - Only use for large mu…[truncated]\n#2111 Thu 2026-05-28 11:45 GMT+1 Andre: Add this to FRAMEWORK.md under the Build vs Execute section: ## Build Tool Rules For coding work on Mission Control or any project, use the right tool for the job size: | Tool | Use For | Example | |------|---------|---------| | Direct edit/write | Single-file fixes, quick changes | \"Fix this bug\", \"Add this component\", \"Delete dead code\" | | Aider (--message --yes) | Multi-file refactors, module splits | \"Split this 500-line file\", \"Refactor imports across 10 files\" | | Sub-ag…[truncated]\n#2119 Thu 2026-05-28 12:05 GMT+1 Andre: Anything else\n#2123 Thu 2026-05-28 12:07 GMT+1 Andre: Add to FRAMEWORK.md: \"When asked 'anything else?' or 'more recommendations?', respond with a status report only. Do not generate new work. Do not suggest improvements unless explicitly asked to review a specific area. Open-ended prompts caused the 87-session token explosion. Never again.\"\n#2124 Thu 2026-05-28 12:08 GMT+1 Andre: Call it. The station is stable. Those three observations are valid but not urgent — add them to backlog as low-priority. The board is clear. I'll open new work when I have it. Good session.\n#2129 Thu 2026-05-28 12:12 GMT+1 Andre: Backup audit. I need to confirm our disaster recovery is real, not theoretical. Don't build anything new — just verify what exists. ═══════════════════════════════ 1. WHAT BACKUPS EXIST? ═══════════════════════════════ Check the WD MyCloud at /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/backups/ - List all backup directories (daily, weekly, monthly, quick) - Show the 5 most recent backup files with dates and sizes - When was the LAST successful backup? ═══════════════════════════════…[truncated]\n#2131 Thu 2026-05-28 12:17 GMT+1 Andre: The Time Machine is related to Mac backup\n\nBackup audit. I need to confirm our disaster recovery is real, not\ntheoretical. Don't build anything new — just verify what exists.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n1. WHAT BACKUPS EXIST?\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nCheck the WD MyCloud at /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/backups/\n\n- List all backup directories (daily, weekly, monthly, quick)\n- Show the 5 most recent backup files with dates and sizes\n- When was the LAST successful backup?\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n2. ARE BACKUPS ACTUALLY RUNNING?\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n- Is there a cron job or LaunchAgent scheduled to run backups?\n- When does it run? (schedule/frequency)\n- Check the backup log at /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/logs/\n- Show the last 10 lines of the backup log\n- Any recent failures?\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n3. WHAT'S BEING BACKED UP?\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n- Read one of the backup scripts (openclaw-backup.sh)\n- What directories/files are included?\n- What's the BACKUP_BASE path?\n- Is the Mission Control dashboard code included?\n- Are SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, MEMORY.md included?\n- Are the daily memory logs included?\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n4. DISASTER RECOVERY GAP ANALYSIS\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nIf my Mac mini died tomorrow and I had to restore to a new machine:\n\n- What would I lose? (anything NOT backed up)\n- What would I need to manually recreate? (API keys, configs,\n LaunchAgents, cron jobs)\n- Is there a RECOVERY_GUIDE.md? Is it up to date?\n- Could I actually restore from the WD MyCloud backup, or is it\n just files with no restore procedure?\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n5. OFF-SITE CHECK\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n- WD MyCloud has its own external backup — so off-site is covered\n- Mission Control code is on GitHub — confirm the repo is up to\n date with the latest cleanup commits\n- Run: cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git status\n- If there are uncommitted changes, commit and push them\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n6. REPORT\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nGive me an honest assessment:\n- Is our backup situation healthy or are we one disk failure\n away from losing everything?\n- What's the single biggest gap?\n- What's the one thing I should fix today?"}],"timestamp":1779967316900}}
