{"type":"message","id":"82faa249","parentId":"c79a9ea3-f221-4a53-b135-a7ececc16b69","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:35:25.156Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:7507878944\",\n  \"message_id\": \"2148\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"sender\": \"Andre\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-05-28 12:35 GMT+1\",\n  \"inbound_event_kind\": \"user_request\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Andre (7507878944)\",\n  \"id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"name\": \"Andre\",\n  \"username\": \"mayhomme\"\n}\n```\n\nConversation context (untrusted, chronological, selected for current message):\n#2100 Thu 2026-05-28 11:36 GMT+1 Andre: 6. AIDER INTEGRATION (IF USEFUL) ═══════════════════════════════ You mentioned Aider could speed up large refactors. If it's worth adding, use it in non-interactive mode: - Install: pip install aider-chat or brew install aider - API key: use our existing OpenRouter key (already in OPENROUTER_API_KEY) - Usage: aider --message \"refactor X across Y files\" --model openrouter/owl-alpha --yes - The --yes flag auto-confirms changes so it runs without interaction - Only use for large mu…[truncated]\n#2111 Thu 2026-05-28 11:45 GMT+1 Andre: Add this to FRAMEWORK.md under the Build vs Execute section: ## Build Tool Rules For coding work on Mission Control or any project, use the right tool for the job size: | Tool | Use For | Example | |------|---------|---------| | Direct edit/write | Single-file fixes, quick changes | \"Fix this bug\", \"Add this component\", \"Delete dead code\" | | Aider (--message --yes) | Multi-file refactors, module splits | \"Split this 500-line file\", \"Refactor imports across 10 files\" | | Sub-ag…[truncated]\n#2119 Thu 2026-05-28 12:05 GMT+1 Andre: Anything else\n#2123 Thu 2026-05-28 12:07 GMT+1 Andre: Add to FRAMEWORK.md: \"When asked 'anything else?' or 'more recommendations?', respond with a status report only. Do not generate new work. Do not suggest improvements unless explicitly asked to review a specific area. Open-ended prompts caused the 87-session token explosion. Never again.\"\n#2124 Thu 2026-05-28 12:08 GMT+1 Andre: Call it. The station is stable. Those three observations are valid but not urgent — add them to backlog as low-priority. The board is clear. I'll open new work when I have it. Good session.\n#2129 Thu 2026-05-28 12:12 GMT+1 Andre: Backup audit. I need to confirm our disaster recovery is real, not theoretical. Don't build anything new — just verify what exists. ═══════════════════════════════ 1. WHAT BACKUPS EXIST? ═══════════════════════════════ Check the WD MyCloud at /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/backups/ - List all backup directories (daily, weekly, monthly, quick) - Show the 5 most recent backup files with dates and sizes - When was the LAST successful backup? ═══════════════════════════════…[truncated]\n#2131 Thu 2026-05-28 12:17 GMT+1 Andre: The Time Machine is related to Mac backup\n#2136 Thu 2026-05-28 12:21 GMT+1 Andre: Backup audit. I need to confirm our disaster recovery is real, not theoretical. Don't build anything new — just verify what exists. ═══════════════════════════════ 1. WHAT BACKUPS EXIST? ═══════════════════════════════ Check the WD MyCloud at /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/backups/ - List all backup directories (daily, weekly, monthly, quick) - Show the 5 most recent backup files with dates and sizes - When was the LAST successful backup? ═══════════════════════════════…[truncated]\n#2140 Thu 2026-05-28 12:24 GMT+1 Andre: Stop. You're in a loop with the Time Machine check. Break out of it. Forget Time Machine. Just check: 1. cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git status 2. ls /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/backups/ 3. tail -20 /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/logs/backup.log Report the output of these three commands. Nothing else.\n#2144 Thu 2026-05-28 12:26 GMT+1 Andre: The backup audit is complete. Time Machine is running and covering full-disk backups to the WD MyCloud. That's sufficient for disaster recovery. The custom backup scripts targeting /Volumes/Public/ are optional — nice to have for quick OpenClaw-specific restores, but not critical since Time Machine already covers everything. Add a note to RECOVERY_GUIDE.md: \"Primary backup: Time Machine to WD MyCloud. Secondary (optional): custom scripts at ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/ope…[truncated]\n\nThe custom OpenClaw backup scripts exist but were never automated.\nTime Machine covers everything, but I want a dedicated OpenClaw-only\nbackup that runs automatically. This gives us a clean, portable restore\npoint independent of Time Machine.\n\nFix:\n\n1. Update the backup scripts to target the correct path:\n - BACKUP_BASE should be /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup\n - Confirm both openclaw-backup.sh and openclaw-backup-quick.sh\n use this path\n\n2. Create a LaunchAgent that runs openclaw-backup-quick.sh daily at 3am.\n - Name it com.openclaw.backup.plist\n - Shell-only — no model calls\n - Log to ~/.openclaw/logs/backup-cron.log\n\n3. Run the backup once now to verify it works end-to-end.\n\n4. Update RECOVERY_GUIDE.md:\n - Document the backup schedule (daily at 3am via LaunchAgent)\n - Document what's included (configs, SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, MEMORY.md,\n daily logs, scripts, workspace)\n - Document how to restore from a backup\n\n5. Report: backup size, location, and confirmation the LaunchAgent\n is loaded and scheduled."}],"timestamp":1779968125150}}
{"type":"message","id":"e1ad38f7","parentId":"82faa249","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:35:50.480Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me get this done. First, where is `/Volumes/Public` and does the WD MyCloud share need to be mounted?"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"04adfa5a-6169-47d3-a73e-b599e53c101e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if /Volumes/Public exists and what's there\nls -la /Volumes/Public/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"/Volumes/Public DOES NOT EXIST\"\necho \"===\"\n# Check what's on the OpenClaw-WD symlink\nls -la /Volumes/OpenClaw-WD/ 2>/dev/null\necho \"===\"\n# Check if the MyCloud share is accessible\nsmbutil view //spacemonkey@MyCloud-1E4N74.local 2>/dev/null | head -10\necho \"===\"\n# Check the Public-1 mount\nls -la /Volumes/Public-1/ 2>/dev/null","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check if /Volumes/Public exists and what's there\\nls -la /Volumes/Public/ 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"/Volumes/Public DOES NOT EXIST\\\"\\necho \\\"===\\\"\\n# Check what's on the OpenClaw-WD symlink\\nls -la /Volumes/OpenClaw-WD/ 2>/dev/null\\necho \\\"===\\\"\\n# Check if the MyCloud share is accessible\\nsmbutil view //spacemonkey@MyCloud-1E4N74.local 2>/dev/null | head -10\\necho \\\"===\\\"\\n# Check the Public-1 mount\\nls -la /Volumes/Public-1/ 2>/dev/null\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":3268,"output":201,"cacheRead":190976,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":194445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779968125165,"responseId":"gen-1779968125-6gmjBVOtcgIpZvoyguVr"}}
