{"type":"message","id":"3eba907a","parentId":"4b755072","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.940Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK, here's the full picture. Everything's healthy on the infrastructure side, and I've done a thorough code review. Here's my consolidated report:\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 Health Check\n\n**Cron Jobs: ✅ Clear** — No stuck jobs. Only 1 active (FreeRide auto-update), 3 disabled.\n\n**Sessions: ✅ Clear** — Only this Telegram session active. No zombies.\n\n**Gateway: ✅ Running** (pid 69189, LaunchAgent active)\n\n**Vite Dev Server: ⚠️ Down** — Port 3000 not responding. The LaunchAgent or `bun run dev` process isn't running. Need to restart it if you want to browse MC.\n\n**OpenClaw: ⚠️ Update available** — Current: 2026.5.20, Latest: 2026.5.26\n\n---\n\n## 📋 Mission Control Code Review — Recommendations\n\n### 🔴 Critical / High Priority\n\n**1. Vite dev server auto-recovery**\nThe dev server is currently down. You should either:\n- Set up a LaunchAgent for `bun run dev --host --port 3000` in the `mission-control-dashboard` dir, or\n- Add a cron/LaunchAgent health check that restarts it if port 3000 is unreachable.\nThis is your most pressing operational issue — MC is unreachable in the browser right now.\n\n**2. Index page shows Dashboard, but `/home` route exists too**\nYou have both `src/routes/index.tsx` (renders `<Dashboard>`) and `src/routes/home.tsx` (a test page with \"Mission Control — /home test\" title). The `/home` route looks like leftover test code. Either remove it or promote it. Having two \"home\" paths is confusing.\n\n**3. Hardcoded agent data on index route**\nThe index route hardcodes 4 agents with static data instead of using `getAgentStatus()` from the server. This means the dashboard overview won't reflect real cron/session state. The `Dashboard.tsx` component does use `useLiveStationData()` for the Agent Office section, but the overview cards at the top use the static loader data. Consider making the entire page poll dynamically.\n\n### 🟡 Medium Priority\n\n**4. Duplicate/confusing navigation**\nThe sidebar has: Dashboard (logo link → `/`), Agent Office (`/visual`), plus 9 other routes. But you also have a `Spacestation` route (`/spacestation.tsx`) with a 892-line `Spacestation.tsx` component that seems like an older version of the Agent Office. Clarify the information architecture:\n- Is `Dashboard` (`/`) the main overview?\n- Is `Agent Office` (`/visual`) the animated living station?\n- Is `Spacestation` (`/spacestation`) a legacy page?\nIf Spacestation is deprecated, remove it or redirect.\n\n**5. Animation system is CSS-only, but RoomCanvas does heavy pixel drawing**\nThe `StationRoom.tsx` uses CSS keyframes for agent sprites (idle pulse, working glow, etc.), which is good for performance. But `RoomCanvas.tsx` has massive draw functions with inline pixel data (500+ lines of `r()`, `p()`, `hline()` calls). This is fragile and hard to maintain. Consider:\n- Moving room drawings to JSON/data files\n- Or rendering the room backgrounds as static images and only animating agent layers on canvas\n- The current approach mixes drawing code with component logic\n\n**6. `data/tasks.json` is read/written via server functions but also exists as a file on disk**\nThe task auto-move logic (5-minute timeout from in-progress to done with no summary) runs client-side in `tasks.tsx`. If two sessions/tabs are open, they could race on saves. The `saveTasks` server function doesn't do any locking. For a single-user setup this is fine, but worth noting.\n\n**7. Memory route reads daily logs from filesystem but `memory/*.md` files are sparse**\nOnly `memory/2026-05-20.md` exists. The Memory page will show mostly empty content. You should either:\n- Backfill some daily logs\n- Or show a nice empty state with guidance\n\n### 🟢 Low Priority / Nice-to-Have\n\n**8. TypeScript errors were fixed (24 → 0) — great!**\nKeep running `tsc --noEmit` before commits. Consider adding a pre-commit hook.\n\n**9. Consistent OKLCH color system — well done**\nThe design system using OKLCH colors throughout is clean and consistent. The muted green (`oklch(0.88 0.18 145)`) for \"online\" status, violet for tasks, cyan for engineer, pink for lifesupport — this works well.\n\n**10. Consider a \"compact mode\" for the sidebar**\nOn smaller screens the sidebar has 11 nav items across 3 sections. A collapsible or icon-only mode would help.\n\n**11. Calendar route is named \"Scheduler\" in the sidebar but the URL is still `/calendar`**\nThe tab says \"Scheduler\" but the route is `/calendar.tsx`. Pick one name and stick with it.\n\n**12. Asset optimization**\nYou have both old sprite sheets (12 `.png` files in `sprites-old/`) and newer `-4x-v2.png` versions. The old folder (3.8 MB) could be cleaned up.\n\n---\n\nWant me to tackle any of these? I'd suggest starting with **#1 (restart dev server)** and **#4 (clarify the navigation architecture)** since those affect usability the most right now."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":116,"output":1227,"cacheRead":59520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60863,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779952876046,"responseId":"gen-1779952876-ZcWtkNvwf7fJybomFu1O"}}
