{"type":"message","id":"33cb7e56","parentId":"892f57a0","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.941Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"These API routes are called via `/api/tasks`, `/api/dispatch`, etc. They work fine as API handlers — the warnings are just TanStack Start complaining they don't export a `Route`. The fix is to rename them with the `-` prefix convention. But that would break the URL routing. Let me check the TanStack Start v8 convention more carefully:\n\nActually, looking at this again, in TanStack Start, files in `src/routes/api/` that export `GET`/`POST`/`PUT`/`DELETE` ARE valid API route handlers. The warnings are because some files use `.tsx` extension but export raw handlers. The fix is to either rename them to `.ts` or keep them as-is since they functionally work. Let me rename the `.tsx` ones to `.ts` and ensure the actual API endpoints match:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"b66f5b6a-67a8-49c9-bdfc-23716d768d2f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && for f in src/routes/api/*.tsx; do base=$(basename \"$f\" .tsx); mv \"$f\" \"src/routes/api/${base}.ts\"; echo \"Renamed $base.tsx → $base.ts\"; done","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && for f in src/routes/api/*.tsx; do base=$(basename \\\"$f\\\" .tsx); mv \\\"$f\\\" \\\"src/routes/api/${base}.ts\\\"; echo \\\"Renamed $base.tsx → $base.ts\\\"; done\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":505,"output":255,"cacheRead":62336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63096,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779958560134,"responseId":"gen-1779958560-smgAooCuPgrJDtnsSfKM"}}
