{"type":"message","id":"a436580e","parentId":"d338d279","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.942Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Actually that pattern won't work. Let me check the TanStart docs for the correct pattern. The files are in `src/routes/api/` — the standard TanStack Start convention IS that directories starting with `_` are ignored, but `api` is a reserved name that should work. The issue is these files export raw `GET`/`POST` handlers instead of using the `createAPIFileRouteHandler` pattern. Let me revert and just rename them with the `-` prefix convention for non-route files:\n\nWait — actually these ARE working API routes. The warnings are just noise. In TanStack Start v8, API routes in `src/routes/api/*.ts` that export `GET`/`POST` etc. ARE valid. But the new version prefers them to not have `.tsx` extension (which I already fixed by renaming to `.ts`). The warnings appearing for `.ts` files means something else is going on. Let me check if the `save-tasks.ts` file was renamed from `.tsx` to `.ts` properly:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"0d3ab8d0-3f93-438a-99ca-b6f5a835454a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && ls -la src/routes/api/","timeout":3},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && ls -la src/routes/api/\", \"timeout\": 3}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":255,"output":254,"cacheRead":79616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80125,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779959152527,"responseId":"gen-1779959152-b286ugLlbeAes1U8av0S"}}
