{"type":"message","id":"9a43687f","parentId":"aed380f5","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.942Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All `.ts` files. The warnings are still showing because these use the raw handler pattern. The actual fix is to add `server.routeFileIgnorePattern` to ignore the specific files that don't export `Route`, OR convert them to proper API route files. The simplest non-breaking fix is to revert my bad vite config change and just add a `routeFileIgnorePattern` that matches files in the `api/` directory. But actually, looking at TanStart docs again — the `routeFileIgnorePattern` is for files that look like routes but shouldn't be. These ARE routes (API routes), they're just using the old pattern.\n\nLet me revert the vite config and check if there's a `server.config.ts` or if I should just live with the warnings since they don't affect functionality:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"f67ac979-1bec-4007-9499-6bb285ee5fea","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/vite.config.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"    routeFileIgnorePattern: \"-api-\" ,","newText":""}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/vite.config.ts\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"    routeFileIgnorePattern: \\\"-api-\\\" ,\", \"newText\": \"\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":700,"output":229,"cacheRead":79744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80673,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779959170026,"responseId":"gen-1779959170-P0wwMnNWRCrBSwLhfpsY"}}
