{"type":"message","id":"1055a958","parentId":"fbf57870","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.944Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Here are my additional recommendations:\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 Additional Recommendations (Round 2)\n\n### 🔴 Should Do Now\n\n**1. `getSystemStats()` has hardcoded `openclawVersion: \"2026.5.7\"`**\nThis is stale (actual version is now 2026.5.6... wait, you updated to 5.26 but this says 5.7). This value should be read dynamically from the actual OpenClaw installation or derived from the config file. Minor but confusing.\n\n**2. `getAllActivityFeed()` reads from `data/activity.json` which doesn't exist**\nThe activity route, Dashboard activity feed, and several places try to load this file. It probably falls back gracefully with an empty array, but you're populating activity via cron/task auto-creation, not via an activity feed writer. The activity feed is essentially always empty. Either start writing to it or remove the feature.\n\n**3. Query cache invalidation every 15s is aggressive**\n`__root.tsx` has `setInterval(() => router.invalidate(), 15000)` — this re-fetches ALL loader data every 15 seconds on every page. On pages like Tasks (which POSTs to save) or Settings (which calls `execSync` for gateway status), this causes unnecessary server load. Most pages only need specific parts refreshed (e.g., Agent Office every 10s via `useLiveStationData`, but the full-page router invalidation should be ~60s or event-driven).\n\n### 🟡 Should Do Soon\n\n**4. `server-data.ts` is 1018 lines — split it up**\nThis file has tasks, queue, cron jobs, activity, memory, docs, projects, incidents, system stats, agent status, quick actions, and OpenClaw status — all in one file. Split into domain modules:\n- `server-data/tasks.ts`\n- `server-data/crons.ts`\n- `server-data/system.ts`\n- `server-data/agents.ts`\n- `server-data/memory-docs-projects.ts`\n- `server-data/incidents.ts`\n- `server-data/quick-actions.ts`\n\n**5. Error boundary shows raw `error.message` to users**\nThe `ErrorComponent` in `__root.tsx` doesn't show the error message to users (good), BUT it only uses generic text. Consider adding an error ID + timestamp for supportability.\n\n**6. The `projects.json` file is tiny (956 bytes) and data is likely stale**\nCheck if the Projects page still works meaningfully or if it's dead content.\n\n**7. Scheduler page is 559 lines — too big**\nSplit the cron error table, job list, and controls into sub-components.\n\n### 🟢 Nice to Have\n\n**8. `task-flow-signals.tsx` is 41 lines but imported nowhere**\n`TaskFlowSignals.tsx` — check if this dead code can be removed.\n\n**9. Accessibility: add `aria-label`s to sidebar nav items**\nThe sidebar links have good visual styling but minimal screen-reader support.\n\n**10. Memory page has no content**\nBackfill a few daily logs from session transcripts, or import the wiki content into daily log format so the Memory page is useful.\n\n**11. Consider dark/light theme toggle**\nCurrently hardcoded to `class=\"dark\"` on `<html>`. The OKLCH color system could support both.\n\n---\n\nWant me to do these too? I'd suggest the **hardcoded version string (#1)**, **empty activity feed (#2)**, and **slow down the 15s invalidation (#3)** first since those are the most impactful. The file splits (#4, #7) are pure refactoring."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":729,"output":803,"cacheRead":93056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94588,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779961143275,"responseId":"gen-1779961143-EhyKOm4lgYfVKY7Atxnk"}}
