{"type":"message","id":"9043eb4d","parentId":"75c4236c","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.947Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK the problem is that both `types.ts` AND the sub-modules export the same type names. When the barrel does `export * from \"./types\"` and `export * from \"./memory\"`, TypeScript sees duplicate `MemoryEntry` etc. The fix is to NOT re-export types from sub-modules — let the barrel be the single source. But the sub-modules DO need those types for their function signatures. The fix: sub-modules import types from `./types` but don't re-export them. The barrel exports everything — functions from sub-modules, types from types.ts.\n\nThe problem is actually my `export * from \"./memory\"` — this re-exports `MemoryEntry` from memory.ts AND types.ts. Since the types are identical, TypeScript should be fine... but it's not because they're from different modules.\n\nLet me just remove the duplicate type definitions from sub-modules and only keep them in types.ts. The sub-modules already import from `./types`, so they just need to NOT define the type locally. Let me check which sub-modules have local type defs:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"409b38ed-80c8-413d-afe6-d1c19d34921a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && grep \"^export interface\\|^export type\" src/lib/server-data/*.ts | grep -v types.ts","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && grep \\\"^export interface\\\\|^export type\\\" src/lib/server-data/*.ts | grep -v types.ts\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":209,"output":271,"cacheRead":141824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":142304,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779963303543,"responseId":"gen-1779963303-fCyto6q2BzYqPpKAMMvW"}}
