{"type":"message","id":"272676ae","parentId":"a69914cf","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.949Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood question. Let me be straightforward about it.\n\n## Why Aider isn't being used\n\n**Short answer:** I don't have Aider installed or available in this environment, and I haven't been told to install or use it.\n\n**Longer answer:** Looking at my available tools, I have `exec` which lets me run shell commands. I *could* potentially launch Aider that way if it were installed. But:\n\n1. **It's not installed** — I'd need you to `pip install aider-chat` or similar first\n2. **It needs API keys** — Aider needs an OpenAI/Anthropic API key configured\n3. **It needs git** — Aider works by making commits per change, which is fine since we have git\n4. **I've been managing without it** — the `edit`/`write`/`exec` tools are sufficient for most tasks, especially with sub-agents for parallel work\n\nThat said, **for the kind of multi-file refactor I just did** (splitting server-data.ts across 14 files with cascading import changes), Aider would have been significantly faster. It would:\n- Hold the full codebase context\n- Make coordinated edits across all files\n- Auto-compile after each change\n- Commit each logical step\n\nEverything I did manually in ~2 hours, Aider could do in one prompted pass.\n\n## What would need to happen\n\nIf you want me to use Aider going forward, I'd need:\n1. `pip install aider-chat` (or `brew install aider`)\n2. An API key configured (OpenAI, Anthropic, or — since you use OpenRouter, that works too)\n3. Agreement on when to use it (large refactors) vs. direct edits (quick fixes)\n\nWant me to set that up, or are you happy with how things are working?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1130,"output":391,"cacheRead":149248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":150769,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"tot