{"type":"message","id":"0a6f5d0f","parentId":"14a81034","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.949Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK here's the thing — Aider is designed as an **interactive terminal TUI app**. I can't easily drive it through exec pipes. The way to use it would be to run it in a persistent tmux/terminal session and check on it, but that's awkward from OpenClaw.\n\n**Better approach:** Let me use Aider's **non-interactive mode** with `--message` flag, which lets me pass a prompt and get results back:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"c702bea2-7110-48e9-a46e-1bc6de1eea2c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && python3 -m aider --model openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha --no-auto-commits --yes --dark-mode --message \"Review the Scheduler page at src/routes/scheduler.tsx. It's 559 lines. The page already has JobsTab and ErrorsTab sub-components inside it, but the SchedulerPage function itself is still 280 lines with a lot of state management, fetching logic, and UI markup inlined. Please:\n\n1. Extract the cron fetching/useEffect logic into a custom hook: useCronData() in src/routes/scheduler/useCronData.ts\n2. Extract the CronJob card rendering into src/routes/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx\n3. Extract the error status management (savedMap, errorItems merging logic) into the hook\n4. Keep SchedulerPage as a thin composition component\n5. Preserve ALL existing functionality, types, and behavior exactly\n6. Use atomic writes (writeFileSync + renameSync) for the cron error status API calls\n7. Run tsc --noEmit after changes to verify no errors\" 2>&1 | tail -40","timeout":300,"yieldMs":120000},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && python3 -m aider --model openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha --no-auto-commits --yes --dark-mode --message \\\"Review the Scheduler page at src/routes/scheduler.tsx. It's 559 lines. The page already has JobsTab and ErrorsTab sub-components inside it, but the SchedulerPage function itself is still 280 lines with a lot of state management, fetching logic, and UI markup inlined. Please:\\n\\n1. Extract the cron fetching/useEffect logic into a custom hook: useCronData() in src/routes/scheduler/useCronData.ts\\n2. Extract the CronJob card rendering into src/routes/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx\\n3. Extract the error status management (savedMap, errorItems merging logic) into the hook\\n4. Keep SchedulerPage as a thin composition component\\n5. Preserve ALL existing functionality, types, and behavior exactly\\n6. Use atomic writes (writeFileSync + renameSync) for the cron error status API calls\\n7. Run tsc --noEmit after changes to verify no errors\\\" 2>&1 | tail -40\", \"timeout\": 300, \"yieldMs\": 120000}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":180,"output":374,"cacheRead":152832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":153386,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779964303223,"responseId":"gen-1779964303-2jTzerszsWmhdfuy2Yb2"}}
