{"type":"message","id":"b2fc55db","parentId":"11159581","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.949Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"dfc9dfce-8d3d-4724-ba5c-1818081ed63c","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 2029 more characters truncat"}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"young-zephyr","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"The refactoring is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:                 \n\n 1 Created src/routes/scheduler/useCronData.ts - Custom hook that encapsulates: \n    • All state management (jobs, errors, loading, toggling, result)            \n    • The fetchCrons function with parallel fetching of cron jobs and saved     \n      error statuses                                                            \n    • The error status merging logic (savedMap, errorItems, auto-clear behavior)\n    • The handleToggle function for enabling/disabling cron jobs                \n    • The updateErrorStatus function with task auto-creation on investigation   \n    • The useEffect with 5-second polling interval                              \n 2 Created src/routes/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx - Extracted component for       \n   rendering individual cron job cards with:                                    \n    • Toggle switch with loading state                                          \n    • Job status pills (ACTIVE/DISABLED, error count)                           \n    • Schedule display                                                          \n    • Last/next run times                                                       \n    • Result message display                                                    \n 3 Simplified src/routes/scheduler.tsx - Now a thin composition component (~180 \n   lines vs 559):                                                               \n    • Uses the useCronData hook                                                 \n    • Renders the page header and tabs                                          \n    • Delegates to JobsTab and ErrorsTab sub-components                         \n    • JobsTab now uses CronJobCard for rendering individual jobs                \n\nAll existing functionality, types, and behavior have been preserved exactly. The\natomic writes requirement for cron error status API calls would need to be      \nimplemented on the server-side API (/api/cron-errors) since the client-side     \nfetch API doesn't support file system operations.                               \n\nTokens: 8.6k sent, 6.7k received.\n\nsrc/routes/scheduler/useCronData.ts\n\nsrc/routes/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx\nApplied edit to src/routes/scheduler.tsx\nApplied edit to src/routes/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx\nApplied edit to src/routes/scheduler/useCronData.ts\nSummarization failed for model openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha: cannot schedule new futures after shutdown\nSummarization failed for model openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha: cannot schedule new futures after shutdown\nsummarizer unexpectedly failed for all models\n","name":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779964652508}}
