{"type":"message","id":"88762267","parentId":"bd70ccce","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.950Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:7507878944\",\n  \"message_id\": \"2100\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"sender\": \"Andre\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-05-28 11:36 GMT+1\",\n  \"inbound_event_kind\": \"user_request\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Andre (7507878944)\",\n  \"id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"name\": \"Andre\",\n  \"username\": \"mayhomme\"\n}\n```\n\nConversation context (untrusted, chronological, selected for current message):\n#2032 Thu 2026-05-28 08:17 GMT+1 Andre: Do all recommendations\n#2047 Thu 2026-05-28 09:53 GMT+1 Andre: Do it all\n#2065 Thu 2026-05-28 10:37 GMT+1 Andre: So any other recommendations\n#2067 Thu 2026-05-28 10:42 GMT+1 Andre: Yes do! Is this using aider?\n#2069 Thu 2026-05-28 10:42 GMT+1 Andre: Should you be using aider to make this easier\n#2081 Thu 2026-05-28 10:59 GMT+1 Andre: Let’s review it, if the task is to time consuming, let’s skip\n#2091 Thu 2026-05-28 11:23 GMT+1 Andre: When finished with the task, why is aider not being used?\n#2094 Thu 2026-05-28 11:26 GMT+1 Andre: Yes, aider was brought in to improve coding and help you out\n#2095 Thu 2026-05-28 11:27 GMT+1 Andre: Everything is to help you out\n\n6. AIDER INTEGRATION (IF USEFUL)\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nYou mentioned Aider could speed up large refactors. If it's worth\nadding, use it in non-interactive mode:\n\n- Install: pip install aider-chat or brew install aider\n- API key: use our existing OpenRouter key (already in OPENROUTER_API_KEY)\n- Usage: aider --message \"refactor X across Y files\" --model openrouter/owl-alpha --yes\n- The --yes flag auto-confirms changes so it runs without interaction\n- Only use for large multi-file refactors (splitting modules,\n renaming across codebase, bulk import cleanup)\n- Do NOT use for quick single-file fixes — those stay with exec\n- Do NOT set up tmux sessions or interactive TUI — non-interactive only\n\nAdd a note to FRAMEWORK.md: \"For multi-file refactors too large for\nexec, use aider --message with --yes flag. Quick fixes stay with\ndirect edits.\"\n\nEvaluate whether this is worth installing now or if our current\ntooling is sufficient. Don't install unless you'll actually use it."}],"timestamp":1779965003241}}
{"type":"message","id":"9338a119","parentId":"88762267","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.950Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nAider is already installed and I just used it successfully on the Scheduler split. So no need to install — it's ready to go.\n\nLet me add the note to FRAMEWORK.md:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"cea0e2a0-f309-437f-b840-aa678589e361","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md 2>/dev/null || echo \"FILE NOT FOUND\"","timeout":3},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"FILE NOT FOUND\\\"\", \"timeout\": 3}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1338,"output":84,"cacheRead":156288,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":157710,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779965003255,"responseId":"gen-1779965003-gnhNQTCH5guqE17TyNGx"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a07fcce7","parentId":"9338a119","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.950Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"cea0e2a0-f309-437f-b840-aa678589e361","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 3221 more characters truncat"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":19,"aggregated":"# FRAMEWORK.md — Framework Selection & Documentation Authority\n\n**Purpose:** Ensure every agent uses the right framework for the right project and the right docs for that framework.\n\n**Documentation Authority:** `SOURCES.md` is the single source of truth for canonical documentation URLs. Always check SOURCES.md before loading any framework docs.\n\n---\n\n## Active Project Stacks\n\n### Mission Control Dashboard\n- **Stack:** TanStack Start + React + Vite + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui\n- **Runtime:** Bun\n- **Repo:** `~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/`\n- **Branch strategy:** `main` = prod (port 3000), `dev` = dev (port 3001)\n- **Correct sources:** See `SOURCES.md` → \"TanStack Start Project\"\n\n---\n\n## Framework Selection Guide\n\n### When to use TanStack Start\n- Full-stack React apps with SSR\n- When you need type-safe routing and server functions\n- Default choice for new projects on this system\n- **Docs:** `https://context7.com/websites/tanstack_start/llms.txt`\n\n### When to use Next.js\n- When inheriting a project that already uses Next.js (e.g., from Lovable)\n- When you need App Router, Server Components, or Server Actions\n- When the project has `next.config.js`\n- **Docs:** `https://context7.com/vercel/next.js/llms.txt`\n\n### When to use SvelteKit\n- When inheriting a project that already uses SvelteKit (e.g., from Replit)\n- When the project has `svelte.config.js`\n- **Docs:** `https://context7.com/sveltejs/kit/llms.txt`\n\n### When to use Astro\n- Content-heavy sites, blogs, documentation\n- When inheriting from an AI generator that chose Astro\n- **Docs:** `https://context7.com/withastro/astro/llms.txt`\n\n### When to use Nuxt\n- Vue-based prototypes (future use)\n- **Docs:** `https://context7.com/nuxt/nuxt/llms.txt`\n\n---\n\n## Anti-Patterns (Framework Contamination)\n\nThese are the mistakes that have happened before and must never happen again:\n\n1. **Next.js patterns in TanStack Start** — App Router, Server Actions, `next/headers` in a TanStack project\n2. **TanStack patterns in Next.js** — TanStack loaders, TanStack Router in a Next.js project\n3. **React hooks in SvelteKit** — `useState`, `useEffect` in `.svelte` files\n4. **Vite SSR assumptions in Next.js** — different runtime pipeline\n5. **Bun-only APIs in Node deployments** — runtime incompatibilities\n\n**The fix:** Always read `SOURCES.md` first. Load only the sources for the detected stack.\n\n---\n\n## Gotchas\n\n### FreeRide Watcher Burns Rate Limits During Pool Exhaustion\n- The `freeride-watcher` LaunchAgent polls OpenRouter every ~16 minutes to test model health\n- When the free model pool is exhausted, each poll generates a 429 + a failed rotation attempt (another 429)\n- This is counterproductive — it burns rate limit quota without providing any value\n- **Mitigation:**\n  - Exponential backoff when `all_keys_exhausted` is detected\n  - Auto-disable after 3 consecutive failures\n  - Manual-only mode during dry spells (`freeride auto` on demand)\n- **Status:** Watcher unloaded on 2026-05-22 due to persistent pool exhaustion. Re-enable manually when pool recovers.\n\n## Related Files\n\n- **SOURCES.md** — Canonical documentation URLs, compatibility matrix, agent rules\n- **AGENTS.md** — Agent work rules (includes source selection rules)","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779965015695}}
{"type":"message","id":"3acda479","parentId":"a07fcce7","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.950Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"20da9198-5dc7-4067-8d43-d7d88ed377c5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## Related Files\n\n- **SOURCES.md** — Canonical documentation URLs, compatibility matrix, agent rules\n- **AGENTS.md** — Agent work rules (includes source selection rules)","newText":"## Aider Integration\n\n**When to use Aider:**\n- Large multi-file refactors too complex for direct `edit`/`write` tools\n- Splitting modules, renaming across codebase, bulk import restructuring\n- Always use non-interactive mode: `aider --message \"...\" --yes`\n\n**When NOT to use Aider:**\n- Quick single-file fixes — use direct `edit`/`write`\n- Tasks requiring browser/visual verification\n- Anything that needs interactive debugging\n\n**Configuration:**\n- Installed: `pip install aider-chat` (v0.82.3 installed)\n- API key: `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` (already configured)\n- Model: `openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha`\n- Config: `~/.aider.conf.yml`\n- Usage: `cd <project> && python3 -m aider --model openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha --no-auto-commits --yes --dark-mode --message \"refactor X across Y files\"`\n- Never use interactive TUI / tmux sessions — non-interactive `--message` only\n- Set `--no-auto-commits` to maintain our own git workflow\n\n## Related Files\n\n- **SOURCES.md** — Canonical documentation URLs, compatibility matrix, agent rules\n- **AGENTS.md** — Agent work rules (includes source selection rules)\n- **FRAMEWORK.md** — This file: framework selection, tooling decisions"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"## Related Files\\n\\n- **SOURCES.md** — Canonical documentation URLs, compatibility matrix, agent rules\\n- **AGENTS.md** — Agent work rules (includes source selection rules)\", \"newText\": \"## Aider Integration\\n\\n**When to use Aider:**\\n- Large multi-file refactors too complex for direct `edit`/`write` tools\\n- Splitting modules, renaming across codebase, bulk import restructuring\\n- Always use non-interactive mode: `aider --message \\\"...\\\" --yes`\\n\\n**When NOT to use Aider:**\\n- Quick single-file fixes — use direct `edit`/`write`\\n- Tasks requiring browser/visual verification\\n- Anything that needs interactive debugging\\n\\n**Configuration:**\\n- Installed: `pip install aider-chat` (v0.82.3 installed)\\n- API key: `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` (already configured)\\n- Model: `openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha`\\n- Config: `~/.aider.conf.yml`\\n- Usage: `cd <project> && python3 -m aider --model openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha --no-auto-commits --yes --dark-mode --message \\\"refactor X across Y files\\\"`\\n- Never use interactive TUI / tmux sessions — non-interactive `--message` only\\n- Set `--no-auto-commits` to maintain our own git workflow\\n\\n## Related Files\\n\\n- **SOURCES.md** — Canonical documentation URLs, compatibility matrix, agent rules\\n- **AGENTS.md** — Agent work rules (includes source selection rules)\\n- **FRAMEWORK.md** — This file: framework selection, tooling decisions\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":980,"output":397,"cacheRead":157568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":158945,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779965015698,"responseId":"gen-1779965015-G22TzXikvUhALZcH0xr2"}}
