{"type":"message","id":"14e88f3b","parentId":"88e7635d","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.950Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"c61305da-f18a-417f-b5f1-429643daf72b","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 85 more characters truncated"}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n   6 - **Sub-agent timeout**: If a sub-agent runs >5 min with no resolution, kill it and add task to backlog\n   7 - **Main agent timeout**: If you spend >10 min debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n   8 - **Always report**: When adding to backlog, include what was tried and the blocker\n   9 - **Use agents**: Offload complex debugging/implementation to subagents. Don't spin your wheels alone.\n+ 10 - **Use Aider**: For large multi-file refactors (splitting modules, bulk renames, import restructuring), use Aider in non-interactive mode: `python3 -m aider --model openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha --no-auto-commits --yes --dark-mode --message \"...\". See FRAMEWORK.md for details. Quick single-file fixes stay with direct edit/write tools.\n  10 \n  11 ## First Run\n  12 \n  13 If `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":10},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779965186155}}
