{"type":"message","id":"4926ba13","parentId":"b776d497","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.951Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"e74b61b8-195f-4807-ae14-df4fc38a914c","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md","edits":[{"oldText":"See **Build Tool Rules** above for when to use Aider vs direct edits vs sub-agents.\n\n## Related Files","newText":"See **Build Tool Rules** above for when to use Aider vs direct edits vs sub-agents.\n\n## Agent Communication Rules\n\n### Status Reports Only\nWhen the user asks \"anything else?\" or \"more recommendations?\", respond with a **status report only**:\n- What was completed\n- What's remaining (if anything)\n- Any blockers\n\n**Do NOT:**\n- Generate new work or recommendations unless explicitly asked to review a specific area\n- Suggest improvements, fixes, or new features unprompted\n- Continue iterating on the same topic after the user has moved on\n\n**Why:** Open-ended \"anything else\" prompts caused the 87-session token explosion. The agent kept generating more recommendations indefinitely. Never again.\n\n### Exceptions\n- If the user explicitly says \"review X\" or \"check Y\" → do the review\n- If there's a critical security/stability issue → flag it immediately\n- If the user asks a direct question → answer it concisely\n\n## Related Files"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"See **Build Tool Rules** above for when to use Aider vs direct edits vs sub-agents.\\n\\n## Related Files\", \"newText\": \"See **Build Tool Rules** above for when to use Aider vs direct edits vs sub-agents.\\n\\n## Agent Communication Rules\\n\\n### Status Reports Only\\nWhen the user asks \\\"anything else?\\\" or \\\"more recommendations?\\\", respond with a **status report only**:\\n- What was completed\\n- What's remaining (if anything)\\n- Any blockers\\n\\n**Do NOT:**\\n- Generate new work or recommendations unless explicitly asked to review a specific area\\n- Suggest improvements, fixes, or new features unprompted\\n- Continue iterating on the same topic after the user has moved on\\n\\n**Why:** Open-ended \\\"anything else\\\" prompts caused the 87-session token explosion. The agent kept generating more recommendations indefinitely. Never again.\\n\\n### Exceptions\\n- If the user explicitly says \\\"review X\\\" or \\\"check Y\\\" → do the review\\n- If there's a critical security/stability issue → flag it immediately\\n- If the user asks a direct question → answer it concisely\\n\\n## Related Files\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":240,"output":296,"cacheRead":170112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":170648,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779966544384,"responseId":"gen-1779966544-FyVCSJ5mFS3vvo3wACtV"}}
{"type":"message","id":"32ec4f63","parentId":"4926ba13","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:20.951Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"e74b61b8-195f-4807-ae14-df4fc38a914c","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 88 more characters truncated"}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  99 - Never use interactive TUI / tmux — `--message` with `--yes` only\n 100 \n 101 See **Build Tool Rules** above for when to use Aider vs direct edits vs sub-agents.\n 102 \n+103 ## Agent Communication Rules\n+104 \n+105 ### Status Reports Only\n+106 When the user asks \"anything else?\" or \"more recommendations?\", respond with a **status report only**:\n+107 - What was completed\n+108 - What's remaining (if anything)\n+109 - Any blockers\n+110 \n+111 **Do NOT:**\n+112 - Generate new work or recommendations unless explicitly asked to review a specific area\n+113 - Suggest improvements, fixes, or new features unprompted\n+114 - Continue iterating on the same topic after the user has moved on\n+115 \n+116 **Why:** Open-ended \"anything else\" prompts caused the 87-session token explosion. The agent kept generating more recommendations indefinitely. Never again.\n+117 \n+118 ### Exceptions\n+119 - If the user explicitly says \"review X\" or \"check Y\" → do the review\n+120 - If there's a critical security/stability issue → flag it immediately\n+121 - If the user asks a direct question → answer it concisely\n+122 \n 103 ## Related Files\n 104 \n 105 - **SOURCES.md** — Canonical documentation URLs, compatibility matrix, agent rules\n 106 - **AGENTS.md** — Agent work rules (includes source selection rules)\n     ...","firstChangedLine":103},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779966587210}}
