{"type":"compaction","id":"b6a2782e","parentId":"b5f3e2b5","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:42:31.152Z","summary":"## Goal\nComplete alluser‑requested recommendations, integrate Aider for large multi‑file refactors, finalize code changes, and document Aider usage.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Output must follow the exact section headers and format specified.\n- Preserve exact file paths, function names, and error messages.\n- Keep each section concise.\n- No additional commentary beyond the required content.\n- Use “(none)” when no constraints are mentioned.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Completed Round 1: cron health check, session cleanup, removed `/home` test route, cleaned `sprites-old/`, renamed `calendar.tsx` → `scheduler.tsx`, added “Agent Office” to sidebar, redirected `/spacestation` → `/visual`, made index page dynamic, implemented atomic writes and locking for task saves, fixed `start-mc.sh`, updated OpenClaw to 2026.5.26.\n- [x] Completed Round 2: split `server-data.ts` (1037 lines) into 14 domain modules + barrel export, enriched activity feed, slowed router invalidation 15 s → 60 s, added aria‑labels to sidebar navigation, removed dead `memory-data.ts`, fixed hardcoded `openclawVersion`, all TypeScript errors resolved (0), all routes verified 200.\n- [x] Completed Round 3: used Aider (v0.82.3, model `openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha`) to split Scheduler page (559 → 319 lines), created `useCronData.ts` hook and `CronJobCard.tsx` component, all functionality preserved, 0 TypeScript errors, compiled cleanly, routes still 200.\n- [x] Documented Aider integration: added notes to `FRAMEWORK.md` and `AGENTS.md`, specified non‑interactive `--message --yes` usage, confirmed Aider is installed and configured.\n\n### In Progress\n- None.\n\n### Blocked\n- None.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **[Use Aider for large multi‑file refactors]** – Aider excels at coordinated edits across many files, automatic compilation, and clean commit history; limited to non‑interactive `--message --yes` mode.\n- **[Direct edit/write for quick fixes]** – For single‑file changes, bug fixes, or visual verification, direct `edit`/`write` tools are faster and simpler.\n- **[Sub‑agent for parallel tasks]** – Used for research, verification, and background processes.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. No further work required; all recommendations completed and pushed.\n2. Continue using the established tooling (direct edit/write for quick tasks, Aider for large refactors).\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-05-27.md\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/routes/home.tsx\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-05-28.md\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/scripts/start-mc.sh\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/AppSidebar.tsx\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/RoomCanvas.tsx\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/build-info.ts\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data.ts\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/activity.ts\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/agent-status.ts\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/crons.ts\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/docs.ts\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/helpers.ts\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/incidents.ts\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/index.ts\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/