{"type":"message","id":"731e7a8d","parentId":"1243dece","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:45:32.436Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file is mostly an image attachment. Let me note — I'm in a restricted memory flush turn. I can only write to `memory/2026-05-28.md`. The backup fix (script edits, LaunchAgent creation, first backup run) needs to happen after the flush restriction lifts.\n\n---\n\n**Status:** I was in the middle of fixing the custom backup scripts when the memory flush kicked in.\n\n**What was done:**\n- Read both `openclaw-backup.sh` and `openclaw-backup-quick.sh`\n- Confirmed both target `/Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup` (doesn't exist)\n- Decided to retarget to `/Volumes/Backups of spacemonkey/OpenClaw` (already mounted, 791GB free)\n- Started writing `openclaw-backup.sh` with updated path — blocked by flush\n\n**What's left (need Andre to re-prompt after flush):**\n1. Update both scripts' `BACKUP_BASE` path\n2. Create `com.openclaw.backup.plist` LaunchAgent (daily 3am)\n3. Create log directory `~/.openclaw/logs/`\n4. Run first backup to verify end-to-end\n5. Update `RECOVERY_GUIDE.md`\n\n**Andre — re-send \"continue backup fix\" when you see this and I'll complete all 5 steps.**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":139,"output":294,"cacheRead":27648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28081,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779968708609,"responseId":"gen-1779968708-P3Sm8AkEkWo7B6jLeeWH"}}
