{"type":"message","id":"f462089f","parentId":"477ef1b4","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:54:50.184Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both external disks are read-only. This is a permissions issue — the `openclaw-agent` account can't write to either mounted volume. I need Andre's help.\n\n---\n\nAndre, here's where we stand:\n\n**Both external disks are mounted but read-only for the `openclaw-agent` account:**\n\n| Disk | Mount | Writable? |\n|------|-------|-----------|\n| WD MyCloud | `/Volumes/WD-MyCloud/` | ❌ Read-only (guest/no-write SMB mount) |\n| 15TB Backup Disk | `/Volumes/Backups of spacemonkey/` | ❌ Read-only (likely SMB/NTFS perms) |\n\n**We need write access to one of them.** Options:\n\n1. **Remount the 15TB disk with write perms** — might need admin credentials (`sudo mount`)\n2. **Remount the WD MyCloud share with write** — needs the spacemonkey password for the SMB share (the guest/no-write mount is what we've got)\n3. **Run the backup as your admin user** — the LaunchAgent would need `UserName` set to your admin account\n\nWhich one works for you? I can't write to either disk without escalation."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":365,"output":258,"cacheRead":47104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47727,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779969258389,"responseId":"gen-1779969258-AXactwXQHoOLlIUIYOrJ"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9eed3a4-f0c8-4e1f-a599-425bd083145f","parentId":"f462089f","timestamp":"2026-05-28T11:54:52.823Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both external disks are read-only. This is a permissions issue — the `openclaw-agent` account can't write to either mounted volume. I need Andre's help.\n\n---\n\nAndre, here's where we stand:\n\n**Both external disks are mounted but read-only for the `openclaw-agent` account:**\n\n| Disk | Mount | Writable? |\n|------|-------|-----------|\n| WD MyCloud | `/Volumes/WD-MyCloud/` | ❌ Read-only (guest/no-write SMB mount) |\n| 15TB Backup Disk | `/Volumes/Backups of spacemonkey/` | ❌ Read-only (likely SMB/NTFS perms) |\n\n**We need write access to one of them.** Options:\n\n1. **Remount the 15TB disk with write perms** — might need admin credentials (`sudo mount`)\n2. **Remount the WD MyCloud share with write** — needs the spacemonkey password for the SMB share (the guest/no-write mount is what we've got)\n3. **Run the backup as your admin user** — the LaunchAgent would need `UserName` set to your admin account\n\nWhich one works for you? I can't write to either disk without escalation."}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"total":0,"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":0,"total_tokens":0,"cache":{"read":0,"write":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779969292821}}
{"type":"message","id":"b3d0c037","parentId":"a9eed3a4-f0c8-4e1f-a599-425bd083145f","timestamp":"2026-05-28T12:19:07.080Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:7507878944\",\n  \"message_id\": \"2156\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"sender\": \"Andre\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-05-28 13:19 GMT+1\",\n  \"inbound_event_kind\": \"user_request\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Andre (7507878944)\",\n  \"id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"name\": \"Andre\",\n  \"username\": \"mayhomme\"\n}\n```\n\nConversation context (untrusted, chronological, selected for current message):\n#2123 Thu 2026-05-28 12:07 GMT+1 Andre: Add to FRAMEWORK.md: \"When asked 'anything else?' or 'more recommendations?', respond with a status report only. Do not generate new work. Do not suggest improvements unless explicitly asked to review a specific area. Open-ended prompts caused the 87-session token explosion. Never again.\"\n#2124 Thu 2026-05-28 12:08 GMT+1 Andre: Call it. The station is stable. Those three observations are valid but not urgent — add them to backlog as low-priority. The board is clear. I'll open new work when I have it. Good session.\n#2129 Thu 2026-05-28 12:12 GMT+1 Andre: Backup audit. I need to confirm our disaster recovery is real, not theoretical. Don't build anything new — just verify what exists. ═══════════════════════════════ 1. WHAT BACKUPS EXIST? ═══════════════════════════════ Check the WD MyCloud at /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/backups/ - List all backup directories (daily, weekly, monthly, quick) - Show the 5 most recent backup files with dates and sizes - When was the LAST successful backup? ═══════════════════════════════…[truncated]\n#2131 Thu 2026-05-28 12:17 GMT+1 Andre: The Time Machine is related to Mac backup\n#2136 Thu 2026-05-28 12:21 GMT+1 Andre: Backup audit. I need to confirm our disaster recovery is real, not theoretical. Don't build anything new — just verify what exists. ═══════════════════════════════ 1. WHAT BACKUPS EXIST? ═══════════════════════════════ Check the WD MyCloud at /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/backups/ - List all backup directories (daily, weekly, monthly, quick) - Show the 5 most recent backup files with dates and sizes - When was the LAST successful backup? ═══════════════════════════════…[truncated]\n#2140 Thu 2026-05-28 12:24 GMT+1 Andre: Stop. You're in a loop with the Time Machine check. Break out of it. Forget Time Machine. Just check: 1. cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git status 2. ls /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/backups/ 3. tail -20 /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/logs/backup.log Report the output of these three commands. Nothing else.\n#2144 Thu 2026-05-28 12:26 GMT+1 Andre: The backup audit is complete. Time Machine is running and covering full-disk backups to the WD MyCloud. That's sufficient for disaster recovery. The custom backup scripts targeting /Volumes/Public/ are optional — nice to have for quick OpenClaw-specific restores, but not critical since Time Machine already covers everything. Add a note to RECOVERY_GUIDE.md: \"Primary backup: Time Machine to WD MyCloud. Secondary (optional): custom scripts at ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/ope…[truncated]\n#2148 Thu 2026-05-28 12:35 GMT+1 Andre: The custom OpenClaw backup scripts exist but were never automated. Time Machine covers everything, but I want a dedicated OpenClaw-only backup that runs automatically. This gives us a clean, portable restore point independent of Time Machine. Fix: 1. Update the backup scripts to target the correct path: - BACKUP_BASE should be /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup - Confirm both openclaw-backup.sh and openclaw-backup-quick.sh use this path 2. Create a LaunchAgent…[truncated]\n#2150 Thu 2026-05-28 12:36 GMT+1 Andre: Check if the WD MyCloud is mounted at /Volumes/Public first. If not, mount it with the guest credentials we've used before. Confirm it's writable before running any backup scripts.\n#2154 Thu 2026-05-28 12:52 GMT+1 Andre: What’s happened\n\nOption 3: Run the backup LaunchAgent as my admin user.\n\n1. Create the LaunchAgent at ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.openclaw.backup.plist\n2. Set UserName to spacemonkey (my admin account) in the plist\n3. Schedule: daily at 3am, runs openclaw-backup-quick.sh\n4. Log to ~/.openclaw/logs/backup-cron.log\n5. Test it by running the backup once now as admin:\n bash ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/openclaw-backup-quick.sh\n\nThe backup scripts target /Volumes/Public/ — if that mount point\nisn't available, mount it first using the guest SMB path we've\nused before: //guest@MyCloud-1E4N74.local/Public\n\nConfirm: backup completes, files are written, LaunchAgent is loaded."}],"timestamp":1779970747074}}
{"type":"message","id":"6eda8b20","parentId":"b3d0c037","timestamp":"2026-05-28T12:20:53.360Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGot it. The key insight is that the LaunchAgent runs as `spacemonkey` (admin) which will have write access to the mounted SMB share. Let me check the mount situation first."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"64390a92-da61-4068-a791-d23b496d83a2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if there's a LaunchAgent we can use for mounting, and what user context we're running as\nwhoami && echo \"---\"\n# Check if spacemonkey admin account exists\ndscl . -read /Users/spacemonkey RealName 2>/dev/null && echo \"---\"\n# Check if there's already a mount for /Volumes/Public\nls -la /Volumes/Public 2>/dev/null || echo \"/Volumes/Public does not exist\"\necho \"---\"\n# Check what's on the WD MyCloud that TimeMachine uses\ntmutil destinationinfo 2>/dev/null | head -10","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check if there's a LaunchAgent we can use for mounting, and what user context we're running as\\nwhoami && echo \\\"---\\\"\\n# Check if spacemonkey admin account exists\\ndscl . -read /Users/spacemonkey RealName 2>/dev/null && echo \\\"---\\\"\\n# Check if there's already a mount for /Volumes/Public\\nls -la /Volumes/Public 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"/Volumes/Public does not exist\\\"\\necho \\\"---\\\"\\n# Check what's on the WD MyCloud that TimeMachine uses\\ntmutil destinationinfo 2>/dev/null | head -10\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":43912,"output":198,"cacheRead":4992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49102,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779970747086,"responseId":"gen-1779970747-h23br4APGvkQ3uTPApLo"}}
