{"type":"message","id":"fe979841","parentId":"abe2eba3","timestamp":"2026-05-28T13:36:46.813Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirmed: both external volumes are read-only for this account. The 15TB disk is mounted read-only (likely due to SMB/NTFS permission mapping). Local writes work fine.\n\nAndre, we're blocked on **two issues**:\n\n1. **`/Volumes/Public` (WD MyCloud):** SMB mount requires a password we can't provide non-interactively. The `mount_smbfs` call gets \"Authentication error.\"\n2. **15TB backup disk:** Mounted read-only. Can't write.\n\nBoth disks need admin intervention. **Here's what I need from you:**\n\n**Option A (fastest):** Mount the WD MyCloud Public share yourself with credentials, point it at `/Volumes/Public`, then I can run everything else (update scripts, create LaunchAgent, test backup).\n\n**Option B:** Give me the MyCloud password so I can pass it to `mount_smbfs` non-interactively.\n\n**Option C:** Remount the 15TB disk as read-write: `sudo mount -uw \"/Volumes/Backups of spacemonkey/\"`.\n\nWhich works best for you? Once I can write to one of these, the rest is ~5 minutes of work (script update, LaunchAgent plist, test run, RECOVERY_GUIDE update)."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":462,"output":268,"cacheRead":51072,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51802,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779975349947,"responseId":"gen-1779975350-UPQndjSm1oklEHckSYjT"}}
