e. Just check: 1. cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git status 2. ls /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/backups/ 3. tail -20 /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup/logs/backup.log Report the output of these three commands. Nothing else.\n#2144 Thu 2026-05-28 12:26 GMT+1 Andre: The backup audit is complete. Time Machine is running and covering full-disk backups to the WD MyCloud. That's sufficient for disaster recovery. The custom backup scripts targeting /Volumes/Public/ are optional — nice to have for quick OpenClaw-specific restores, but not critical since Time Machine already covers everything. Add a note to RECOVERY_GUIDE.md: \"Primary backup: Time Machine to WD MyCloud. Secondary (optional): custom scripts at ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/ope…[truncated]\n#2148 Thu 2026-05-28 12:35 GMT+1 Andre: The custom OpenClaw backup scripts exist but were never automated. Time Machine covers everything, but I want a dedicated OpenClaw-only backup that runs automatically. This gives us a clean, portable restore point independent of Time Machine. Fix: 1. Update the backup scripts to target the correct path: - BACKUP_BASE should be /Volumes/Public/openclaw-agent-backup - Confirm both openclaw-backup.sh and openclaw-backup-quick.sh use this path 2. Create a LaunchAgent…[truncated]\n#2150 Thu 2026-05-28 12:36 GMT+1 Andre: Check if the WD MyCloud is mounted at /Volumes/Public first. If not, mount it with the guest credentials we've used before. Confirm it's writable before running any backup scripts.\n#2154 Thu 2026-05-28 12:52 GMT+1 Andre: What’s happened\n#2156 Thu 2026-05-28 13:19 GMT+1 Andre: Option 3: Run the backup LaunchAgent as my admin user. 1. Create the LaunchAgent at ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.openclaw.backup.plist 2. Set UserName to spacemonkey (my admin account) in the plist 3. Schedule: daily at 3am, runs openclaw-backup-quick.sh 4. Log to ~/.openclaw/logs/backup-cron.log 5. Test it by running the backup once now as admin: bash ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/openclaw-backup-quick.sh The backup scripts target /Volumes/Public/ — if that mount point isn't…[truncated]\n#2159 Thu 2026-05-28 14:33 GMT+1 Andre: .\n\nHi"}],"timestamp":1779976010542}}
{"type":"message","id":"6e3f55e8","parentId":"1f7323d7","timestamp":"2026-05-28T13:47:29.828Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHey Andre. Quick status on the backup fix:\n\n**Blocker:** Both external disks are read-only for this account, and the WD MyCloud SMB share needs a password I don't have.\n\n| Disk | Mount | Writable? | Issue |\n|------|-------|-----------|-------|\n| WD MyCloud Public | Not mounted | — | `mount_smbfs` needs password |\n| WD MyCloud OpenClaw | `/Volumes/WD-MyCloud/` | ❌ Read-only | Guest/no-write mount |\n| 15TB Backup Disk | `/Volumes/Backups of spacemonkey/` | ❌ Read-only | SMB perms |\n\n**I need you to do one of:**\n\n1. **Mount `/Volumes/Public` yourself** (with WD MyCloud credentials) → I do the rest\n2. **Remount the 15TB disk read-write:** `sudo mount -uw \"/Volumes/Backups of spacemonkey/\"` → I do the rest  \n3. **Give me the MyCloud password** → I mount and do the rest\n\nOnce I can write to a backup target, the remaining work is quick:\n1. Update `BACKUP_BASE` in both scripts\n2. Create `com.openclaw.backup.plist` (daily 3am, logs to `~/.openclaw/logs/backup-cron.log`)\n3. Run first backup to verify\n4. Update `RECOVERY_GUIDE.md`\n\nWhat's easiest for you?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":47842,"output":314,"cacheRead":4992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53148,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779976010555,"responseId":"gen-1779976010-cWxUHWD5FFlvk8sbQjRS"}}
